name: 1.20 Oxo Tower Wharf
description:
A Victorian chocolate factory conversion with exposed girders, brickwork and Crittal-style windows. 

No 50 was transformed from a flat into a traditional, bespoke shoemaking workshop, showroom and shoe & leather craft training school.
address: Unit 1.20 Oxo Tower Wharf, Bargehouse Street , SE1 9PH

name: Kingston Guildhall and History Centre
description: Built in the Georgian style, the Guildhall brought together Kingston's administrative functions. Purpose-built Magistrates Courts were included in the building, part of which are now home to Kingston History Centre.
address: High Street , Kingston upon Thames, KT1 1EU
